  "market_context": "Crude Oil Futures on the daily chart after a rally into a fair value gap around the 94-96 area, followed by a sharp displacement lower. Price then retraced upward to retest a bearish order block formed during the displacement.",
  "key_observation": "After price retested the bearish order block, an up-close candle entered the zone and the following candle closed below it, forming a propulsion block (an order block off another order block) with a highly sensitive opening price.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Identified price reaching into a fair value gap on the daily chart, marking an important level.",
    "Noted a series of up-close candles into the FVG, followed by displacement lower that closed below the up-close series, validating a bearish order block.",
    "Observed price retracing back up to retest the bearish order block.",
    "Identified the up-close candle that retested the order block, and waited for the next candle to close below it, validating a propulsion block.",
    "Defined entry at the opening price of the propulsion block, with stop on the other side of the body (preferred) or above the high.",
    "Set target at 2R, which aligns with the prior swing low, or alternatively dropping to a lower time frame for refined targeting."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "A propulsion block forms when an order block develops off another order block on retest. Entry at the opening price with stop beyond the body provides a tight, high-probability setup; the mean threshold must not be broken.",
